    <div class="rounded-lg border border-purple-800/40 bg-purple-900/10 p-4 mb-6">
      <p class="text-sm text-purple-300 font-medium mb-2">🧠 Why Daily Words Work</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Research shows that learning one word per day with context (meaning + usage) leads to significantly better retention than cramming word lists. The Word of the Day uses spaced exposure — you see it, you look it up, you save it, and you encounter it again in Memory WordBench and your Memory WordBench. Each repetition strengthens the neural pathway.</p>
